{"lemma":"صَدَقاتُ","slug":"صَدَقاتُ","root":"ص.د.ق","root_slug":"ص-د-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-د-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَدَقَة","root":"صدق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":13},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23997","n24004","n24005","n24006","n24007","n24008"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alms; charitable gift; charity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dowry","examples":[{"text":"وَآتُوا ٱلنِّسَاءَ صَدُقَاتِهِنَّ نِحْلَةً","english":"And give unto the women (whom ye marry) free gift of their marriage portions (Pickthall)"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic צְדַקְתָּא (ṣǝḏaqtā), from the root equalling the Arabic root ص د ق (ṣ d q). Cognate to Hebrew צְדָקָה (ṣədāqā)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.da.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23997","headword_ar":"صدّقهُ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSodiyqN","text_ar":"تَصْدِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*~abahu","text_ar":"كَذَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, * K.) [This explanation implies several meanings here following.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascribed, to him truth, veracity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the speaking truth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast spoken truth."},{"kind":"text","text":"” (Msb.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He accepted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assented to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"believed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what he said:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sd~qhu fiY Hadiyvihi","text_ar":"صدّقهُ فِى حَدِيثِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He accepted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what he said in his information,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narration"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sd~q bilisaAnihi","text_ar":"صدّق بِلِسَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He assented to the truth of what was said with his tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biqalobihi","text_ar":"بِقَلْبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aamn","text_ar":"اَمن"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He held him to be a speaker of truth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He found him to be a speaker of truth. He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, proved him to be a speaker of truth; verified him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confirmed the truth of what he said:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonN","text_ar":"بَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He found it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an opinion)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veritable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh and Bd and Jel, in xxxiv. 19.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He verified it; confirmed its truth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved it to be true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veritable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. an opinion [&c.]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~aqahu","text_ar":"حَقَّقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ksh and Bd, ibid.:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sad~aqa Alxabara Alxuboru","text_ar":"صَدَّقَ الخَبَرَ الخُبْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The trial, proof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"test, verified the information"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbr","text_ar":"خبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See 1, near the end. In the saying in the Kur [xxxix. 34],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iY jaA='a biAlS~idoqi","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِى جَا=ءَ بِالصِّدْقِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSad~aqa bihi","text_ar":"وَصَدَّقَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which seems to be best rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But he who hath brought the truth and"},{"kind":"text","text":"he who"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath accepted it as the truth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*~aba biAlA^amori","text_ar":"كَذَّبَ بِالاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] 'Alee the son of Aboo-Tálib is related to have said that by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*Y jA=' bAlSdq","text_ar":"الذى جا=ء بالصدق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant Mohammad; and by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*Y Sd~q bh","text_ar":"الذى صدّق به"},{"kind":"text","text":", Aboo-Bekr: or, as some say, Gabriel and Mohammad [are meant by the former and the latter respectively]: or by the former, Mohammad; and by the latter, [every one of] the believers: (M:) accord. to Er-Rághib, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wSd~q bh","text_ar":"وصدّق به"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and hath found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, to be true"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~aqa","text_ar":"حَقَّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which he hath brought by word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by that which he hath aimed at ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA taHar~aAhu","text_ar":"بِمَا تَحَرَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") by deed. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sd~q","text_ar":"صدّق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ This thing is the truth; ” like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~aqa","text_ar":"حَقَّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hq","text_ar":"حق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  And this verb also denotes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmubaAlagapu fiY AlS~idoqi","text_ar":"المُبَالَغَةُ فِى الصِّدْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Sad~aqato fiyhimo ZunuwniY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My opinions respecting them were,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved to be, very true"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ksh, in xxxiv. 19.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sd~q AlwaHo$iY~u","text_ar":"صدّق الوَحْشِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadaqa","text_ar":"صَدَقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a copy of the M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wild animal ran without looking aside, when charged upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attacked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K, TA:) mentioned by IDrd. (O, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sad~aqahumo","text_ar":"صَدَّقَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exacted from them the poor-rate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaqapN","text_ar":"صَدَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  See also 5."}],"source_refs":["M","S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n24004","headword_ar":"صَدْقَةٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaAqN","text_ar":"صَدَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; each in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24005","headword_ar":"صُدْقَةٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaAqN","text_ar":"صَدَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; each in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24006","headword_ar":"صَدَقَةٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An alms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gift"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the poor"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sake of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to obtain a recompense from God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * Mgh, K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion which a man gives forth from his property by way of propitiation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to obtain the favour of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaApN","text_ar":"زَكَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", except that the former is primarily applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as as is supererogatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter to such as is obligatory: but it is said to be applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is obligatory"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaAp","text_ar":"زَكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor-rate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amount, of property, that is given therefrom, as the due of God, by its possessor, to the poor, according to a fixed rate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] when the person who does so aims at conformity with the truth in his deed: (Er-Rághib, TA:) [in this latter sense, which is indicated in the S and O &c., and more plainly in the M, it is very frequently used:] and thus it is used in the Kur ix. 104, and in like manner its pl. in ix. 60: (Er-Rághib, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaqaAtN","text_ar":"صَدَقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, O, Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Sadaqapa fiY AlA_ibili AljaAr~api","text_ar":"لَا صَدَقَةَ فِى الاـِبِلِ الجَارَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no poorrate in the case of working camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because they are the riding-camels of the people; for the poorrate is in the case of pasturing camels, exclusively of the working. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jr","text_ar":"جر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaAqN","text_ar":"صَدَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","O","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n24007","headword_ar":"صَدُقَةٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaAqN","text_ar":"صَدَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24008","headword_ar":"صُدُقَةٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}